cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a novel approach for salient object detection in panoramic images using spatial density estimation, region growing algorithm, eye fixation model, and geodesic distance refinement. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human perception and visual search mechanism, which suggests the possibility of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of panoramic images and VR/AR technology may also indicate the relevance to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the proposed approach involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which may suggest the relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
